For the following to work you have to setup a Developer version of LaueG on your PC.

======== Building a new installation *.exe file for LaueG ========

In the "My Stuff" menu of LaueG (Developer mode), run:
	"Save Source"
	"Create Release Code"
	"Generate Build Folder"

Run "WindowsInstall.iss" in LaueG\_Release\ which will start Inno Setup
	Use "Build"->"Compile" to create LaueG_setup_<date>.exe in _Release\Installs\
